WEBVTT

00:04.925 --> 00:06.837
[ FILM PROJECTOR CLICKING ]

00:06.837 --> 00:11.392
[ COINS JINGLING ]

00:12.683 --> 00:14.185
[ BELL JINGLES ]

00:15.686 --> 00:17.558
[ CASH REGISTER BELL DINGS ]

00:17.558 --> 00:21.852
Meredith: THEY SAY LIFE DOESN'T
GIVE YOU SECOND CHANCES.

00:24.985 --> 00:27.448
BUT WE DO.

00:29.150 --> 00:31.072
SURGEONS DO.

00:31.072 --> 00:32.533
HEY. E.R.?
YEP.

00:32.533 --> 00:34.865
UH, SO,
SORRY ABOUT LAST NIGHT.

00:34.865 --> 00:36.207
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

00:36.207 --> 00:37.328
YOU'RE MAD.

00:37.328 --> 00:38.829
WE JUST --
WE REALLY LOST TRACK OF TIME --

00:38.829 --> 00:39.830
I'M NOT. IT'S FINE.

00:39.830 --> 00:41.082
FORGET IT.
OH.

00:41.082 --> 00:43.003
YOU BREAK A BONE,
WE PUT IT BACK TOGETHER.

00:43.003 --> 00:45.716
YOU BLEED, WE MAKE IT STOP.
Nicole: WELL?

00:45.716 --> 00:47.428
YOU FLATLINE,
WE RESUSCITATE YOU.

00:47.428 --> 00:48.429
WHAT DID YOU DECIDE?

00:48.429 --> 00:50.671
I DIDN'T!
I WAS UP ALL NIGHT.

00:50.671 --> 00:52.263
THEN YOU HAD AMPLE TIME.

00:52.263 --> 00:54.805
YOU CAN'T DROP A BOMB LIKE
"I HAVE A BRAIN TUMOR"

00:54.805 --> 00:56.227
AND EXPECT ME
TO DECIDE ANYTHING.

00:56.227 --> 00:57.558
I NEED TO KNOW MORE.

00:57.558 --> 00:59.940
YOU DON'T NEED TO KNOW ANYTHING
THAT YOU DON'T ALREADY KNOW.

00:59.940 --> 01:01.232
OKAY, GREAT.
WHY THE PILLS?

01:01.232 --> 01:02.773
I'M GETTING A MIGRAINE.

01:02.773 --> 01:04.024
YOU'RE NOT HELPING.

01:04.024 --> 01:06.237
THIS --
THIS IS WHAT I MEAN.

01:06.237 --> 01:08.028
IS IT A MIGRAINE
OR IS IT THE TUMOR?

01:08.028 --> 01:09.610
WHAT KIND OF TUMOR IS IT?
WHAT DOES IT MEAN?

01:09.610 --> 01:11.572
A-ARE YOU -- ARE YOU GONNA GET
TREMORS DURING SURGERY?

01:11.572 --> 01:12.993
YOU'RE TALKING ME THROUGH
A PROCEDURE

01:12.993 --> 01:14.155
AND YOU SLUR YOUR SPEECH?

01:14.155 --> 01:15.156
I NEED TO KNOW MORE!

01:15.156 --> 01:16.907
YOU DON'T GET TO.

01:16.907 --> 01:18.829
OF COURSE I'M NOT GONNA
DO ANYTHING

01:18.829 --> 01:20.201
TO ENDANGER MY PATIENTS.

01:20.201 --> 01:23.083
I AM HANDLING MY SITUATION
RESPONSIBLY,

01:23.083 --> 01:27.258
BUT IT IS MY SITUATION,
AND YOU ARE NOT ENTITLED TO IT.

01:27.258 --> 01:30.511
YOU ARE ENTITLED
TO MY KNOWLEDGE --

01:30.511 --> 01:36.056
TO MY YEARS OF DISCOVERIES
AND MISTAKES AND DEAD ENDS

01:36.056 --> 01:39.850
AND BLOOD AND SWEAT
AND INNOVATIONS

01:39.850 --> 01:41.772
THAT YOU DON'T HAVE TO
GO THROUGH.

01:41.772 --> 01:43.023
THAT'S THE DEAL.

01:43.023 --> 01:48.439
THE CHANCE TO TAKE MY WORK
INTO YOUR FUTURE.

01:48.439 --> 01:52.533
JUST YOU.

01:52.533 --> 01:54.074
SO...

01:54.074 --> 01:57.328
COULD YOU PLEASE
MAKE UP YOUR MIND?

01:57.328 --> 02:00.581
BUT AS MUCH AS WE GIVE PEOPLE
SECOND CHANCES,

02:00.581 --> 02:03.914
SURGEONS DON'T USUALLY
GET THEM.

02:03.914 --> 02:06.297
SURGERIES ARE CANCELED.

02:06.297 --> 02:09.340
ROUND ON MY SERVICE.
I HAVE AN APPOINTMENT.

02:09.340 --> 02:11.051
AND DON'T ASK WHAT IT IS,

02:11.051 --> 02:14.014
'CAUSE, OF COURSE,
I'M NOT GONNA TELL YOU.

02:14.014 --> 02:16.056
BECAUSE THE KIND OF MISTAKES
WE MAKE

02:16.056 --> 02:18.389
ARE SOMETIMES IMPOSSIBLE
TO RECOVER FROM.

02:18.389 --> 02:20.811
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

02:20.811 --> 02:23.604
UH -- [ CLEARS THROAT ]
I WAS -- I WAS UP ALL NIGHT.

02:23.604 --> 02:24.685
ME TOO.

02:24.685 --> 02:26.527
AH,
SOFIA'S BEEN ACTING OUT,

02:26.527 --> 02:29.029
ASKING QUESTIONS
ABOUT ME AND ARIZONA,

02:29.029 --> 02:31.151
AND I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO TELL HER

02:31.151 --> 02:32.733
OR HOW TO TELL HER,
SO I'M JUST NOT SLEEPING.

02:32.733 --> 02:33.984
I'M MISERABLE.
WHY DIDN'T YOU SLEEP?

02:33.984 --> 02:36.657
OH,
YOU DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

02:36.657 --> 02:39.039
WHAT'S GOING ON?

02:39.039 --> 02:41.081
DEREK AND I WERE UP
HAVING SEX ALL NIGHT.

02:41.081 --> 02:43.204
YEAH, I KIND OF DIDN'T WANT
TO HEAR THAT.

02:43.204 --> 02:45.246
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

02:48.088 --> 02:49.460
69-YEAR-OLD MALE,

02:49.460 --> 02:52.553
JUMPED TWO STORIES
FROM A BURNING BUILDING.

02:52.553 --> 02:56.136
SHOCKY, B.P.'s 95 OVER 60
WITH A RATE IN THE 120s.

02:56.136 --> 02:57.718
G.C.S. 14 IN THE FIELD.

02:57.718 --> 02:59.059
HATTIE...

02:59.059 --> 03:01.932
WHY AM I LOOKING AT TWO PATIENTS
ON ONE GURNEY?

03:01.932 --> 03:03.143
SHE'S DEAD.
Owen: WHAT?

03:03.143 --> 03:05.185
HATTIE...
WE COULDN'T FIND
A PULSE.

03:05.185 --> 03:07.107
AND WE TRIED
TO PULL HER OFF,

03:07.107 --> 03:09.109
BUT THE HUSBAND
JUST HELD ON.

03:09.109 --> 03:11.111
HE WAS AGITATED.
HE WOULDN'T LET HER GO.

03:11.111 --> 03:12.363
SO WE HAD TO STOP

03:12.363 --> 03:14.154
'CAUSE WE WERE AFRAID
WE WERE GONNA HURT HIM.

03:14.154 --> 03:15.656
WHAT'VE WE GOT --
OH, WOW.

03:15.656 --> 03:17.698
HATTIE...
WITNESSES SAID
HE CARRIED HIS WIFE

03:17.698 --> 03:19.700
OUT THE WINDOW AND JUMPED
TO ESCAPE THE FIRE.

03:19.700 --> 03:21.532
WE THINK HE WAS TRYING
TO BREAK HER FALL.

03:21.532 --> 03:23.824
LET'S GET THEM
INTO TRAUMA ONE.

03:23.824 --> 03:25.085
AMY,
WHERE DO YOU NEED ME?

03:25.085 --> 03:26.787
YOU GOT THE HEAD LAC
IN BED 3, RIGHT?

03:26.787 --> 03:28.038
YEAH, THAT'S NOTHING.
I CAN JUMP IN ON THIS.

03:28.038 --> 03:29.039
I DON'T NEED YOU.

03:29.039 --> 03:30.381
IS THAT GOOD MANAGEMENT,

03:30.381 --> 03:32.463
YOU LEAVING YOUR STAR PLAYER
ON THE BENCH?

03:32.463 --> 03:33.884
YOU WON'T BE FOR LONG.

03:33.884 --> 03:36.427
PEOPLE ARE ALWAYS HITTING
THEIR HEADS ON SOMETHING.

03:39.099 --> 03:40.261
Meredith: HIS SKIN IS MOTTLED
AND CYANOTIC.

03:40.261 --> 03:41.262
WE HAVE TO GET HER
OFF OF HIM.

03:41.262 --> 03:42.393
Owen: SIR,
YOU HAVE TO LET HER GO.

03:42.393 --> 03:43.934
NO.

03:43.934 --> 03:45.266
WE HAVE TO MOVE HER
TO HELP YOU.
NO, NO.

03:45.266 --> 03:47.107
SIR, WHAT IS YOUR NAME?
NORRIS.

03:47.107 --> 03:49.480
I-IS SHE...?
NORRIS...

03:49.480 --> 03:51.231
YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT THAT RIGHT NOW, SIR.

03:51.231 --> 03:53.153
NO, HE DOES, ACTUALLY.
OF COURSE HE DOES.

03:53.153 --> 03:55.155
NORRIS,
WHAT IS YOUR WIFE'S NAME?
IS SHE...?

03:55.155 --> 03:56.277
HARRIET.

03:56.277 --> 03:58.359
HATTIE.

03:59.700 --> 04:02.162
NORRIS.

04:02.162 --> 04:04.785
NORRIS, IT'S TIME
TO LET HATTIE GO. SHE'S GONE.

04:04.785 --> 04:06.327
GONE?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN GONE?

04:06.327 --> 04:08.078
NORRIS, SHE DIED.

04:08.078 --> 04:09.790
NO. NO.

04:09.790 --> 04:10.921
SHE'S GONE. I'M SORRY.

04:10.921 --> 04:12.172
HATTIE, NO...

04:12.172 --> 04:13.334
YOU DID EVERYTHING
YOU COULD.

04:13.334 --> 04:14.425
NO! NO...

04:14.425 --> 04:15.836
YOU HELPED HER
THROUGH THE HARDEST PART.

04:15.836 --> 04:18.088
YOU HELD HER,
YOU PROTECTED HER,

04:18.088 --> 04:20.050
AND SHE DIED IN YOUR ARMS.

04:20.050 --> 04:22.553
AND I'M SURE SHE COULDN'T THINK
OF A BETTER WAY TO GO.

04:22.553 --> 04:24.345
SHE'S NO LONGER IN ANY PAIN,
NORRIS, BUT YOU ARE,

04:24.345 --> 04:26.226
AND SHE WOULDN'T WANT YOU
TO BE.

04:26.226 --> 04:29.019
YOU HAVE TO LET HER GO NOW
SO WE CAN HELP YOU, OKAY?

04:29.019 --> 04:31.061
[ SOBBING ]

04:31.061 --> 04:33.694
SHE'S MINE.
I CAN'T.

04:33.694 --> 04:37.398
NORRIS.
NORRIS, I'M SO SORRY.

04:37.398 --> 04:38.569
IT'S TIME.

04:49.209 --> 04:50.871
OKAY.

04:50.871 --> 04:52.042
ON 3 --

04:52.042 --> 04:55.676
1...2...3.

04:55.676 --> 04:58.969
Owen:
LET'S GO. COME ON.

04:58.969 --> 05:00.921
I'LL GO PRONOUNCE.
HATTIE...

05:00.921 --> 05:03.263
HATTIE...

05:03.263 --> 05:05.426
HONEY...HONEY...

05:05.426 --> 05:07.478
AIRWAY'S INTACT,
BUT THERE'S A LITTLE SOOT.

05:07.478 --> 05:08.929
HYPOTENSIVE
AND A RIGID ABDOMEN.

05:08.929 --> 05:10.691
PUPILS ARE EQUAL
AND REACTIVE BILATERALLY.

05:10.691 --> 05:12.022
Callie: RIGHT LOWER LEG
IS TENSE AND SWOLLEN.

05:12.022 --> 05:13.854
I'M GONNA MEASURE
COMPARTMENT PRESSURES.

05:13.854 --> 05:15.025
QUIET.
BREATH SOUND
IS DECREASED ON THE LEFT.

05:15.025 --> 05:16.697
ADD RIGHT TIB/FIB
TO THE TRAUMA FILMS.

05:16.697 --> 05:19.029
QUIET!

05:19.029 --> 05:20.531
I GOT A PULSE.

05:20.531 --> 05:22.783
BARELY PALPABLE,
BUT IT'S THERE.

05:22.783 --> 05:24.034
Owen: TRAUMA TWO!

05:24.034 --> 05:25.996
PIERCE, SHEPHERD,
YOU'RE WITH ME.

05:25.996 --> 05:27.498
SHE'S ALIVE?

05:27.498 --> 05:28.539
SHE IS.

05:28.539 --> 05:31.251
YOU'LL TAKE CARE OF HER?

05:31.251 --> 05:33.213
I WILL.

05:33.213 --> 05:35.626
I'LL TAKE REAL GOOD CARE OF HER.
I PROMISE.

05:37.838 --> 05:39.460
WHERE'S DR. HERMAN?

05:39.460 --> 05:41.221
DID YOU CALL MY MOM?

05:41.221 --> 05:43.263
YOU SAID TO WAIT UNTIL THERE'S
SOMETHING TO BE WORRIED ABOUT.

05:43.263 --> 05:45.345
WELL, NOW I'M WORRIED.

05:45.345 --> 05:47.678
WHY ISN'T SHE MOVING?

05:47.678 --> 05:49.059
EMILY, COREY,
I'M CONCERNED

05:49.059 --> 05:51.852
THAT THE BABY MIGHT BE BLEEDING
INTO THE TUMOR ITSELF,

05:51.852 --> 05:53.273
AND IT'S CAUSING HER
TO BE ANEMIC.

05:53.273 --> 05:55.145
OH, MY GOD.
WILL SHE BE ALL RIGHT?

05:55.145 --> 05:56.356
WHERE'S DR. HERMAN?

05:56.356 --> 06:00.481
SHE HAD AN, UM -- AN APPOINTMENT
WITH ANOTHER PATIENT.

06:00.481 --> 06:02.573
WELL, SHE CAN DO SOMETHING,
RIGHT?

06:02.573 --> 06:05.115
SHE SAID SHE'D DO EVERYTHING
TO GET THE BABY TO TERM.

06:05.115 --> 06:07.157
THAT WAS THE WHOLE POINT
OF PLANNING FETAL SURGERY.

06:07.157 --> 06:09.119
AND THAT'S STILL --
THAT'S STILL THE POINT.

06:09.119 --> 06:12.162
DR. HERMAN WILL LIKELY PERFORM
AN INTRAUTERINE TRANSFUSION.

06:12.162 --> 06:13.373
I WILL APPRISE HER,
AND WE'LL COME BACK

06:13.373 --> 06:14.915
AND TALK TO YOU ABOUT
HOW TO MOVE FORWARD.

06:14.915 --> 06:16.997
SIT TIGHT, OKAY?
OKAY.

06:20.090 --> 06:21.261
WHERE IS DR. HERMAN?

06:21.261 --> 06:23.093
NO IDEA,
BUT SHE BETTER PICK UP,

06:23.093 --> 06:25.345
BECAUSE EMILY JENSEN'S BABY'S
GONNA DIE.

06:25.345 --> 06:26.847
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

06:26.847 --> 06:28.178
GOOD TUBE PLACEMENT.

06:28.178 --> 06:30.350
YEAH, THE HEMOPNEUMOTHORAX
IS BIGGER.

06:30.350 --> 06:32.352
EDWARDS,
PREP FOR A CHEST TUBE.

06:32.352 --> 06:34.435
BEFORE YOU DO THAT, EDWARDS,
CAN YOU CHECK WITH C.T. AGAIN

06:34.435 --> 06:35.686
AND SEE
WHEN THEY CAN TAKE US?

06:35.686 --> 06:36.977
BUT SHE'S BLEEDING
INTO HER LUNG.

06:36.977 --> 06:39.480
I KNOW, BUT I FELT A DEPRESSED
TEMPORAL BONE FRACTURE,

06:39.480 --> 06:41.482
AND SHE HAS SPINAL FLUID
COMING OUT OF HER EAR.

06:41.482 --> 06:42.523
I NEED A C.T. TO CONFIRM.

06:42.523 --> 06:43.984
April: I'M ON MY WAY UP
TO RADIOLOGY.

06:43.984 --> 06:45.235
IS ANYONE FREE
TO UPDATE THE FAMILY?

06:45.235 --> 06:47.788
MM-HMM.

06:52.412 --> 06:53.794
SARAH?

06:53.794 --> 06:56.416
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
AMELIA.

06:56.416 --> 06:58.088
YOU'RE...A DOCTOR?

06:58.088 --> 07:00.591
I AM, YEAH.

07:00.591 --> 07:03.594
MY PARENTS,
THEY WERE IN A FIRE.

07:03.594 --> 07:05.506
OH, GOD.

07:05.506 --> 07:07.347
OKAY. UM...

07:07.347 --> 07:09.259
THIS IS WHAT WE KNOW
SO FAR.

07:09.259 --> 07:12.142
YOUR FATHER HAS
SOME INTERNAL INJURIES

07:12.142 --> 07:13.764
AND A LEG FRACTURE.

07:13.764 --> 07:16.186
YOUR MOM HAS SOME BLEEDING
INTO HER LUNG

07:16.186 --> 07:17.357
AND A CRANIAL FRACTURE.

07:17.357 --> 07:20.440
AS HER NEUROSURGEON, I'M GONNA
NEED TO DO SURGERY TO --

07:20.440 --> 07:21.401
WAIT.

07:21.401 --> 07:25.986
YOU...WANT TO DO SURGERY
ON MY MOM?

07:25.986 --> 07:27.367
NO. NO.

07:27.367 --> 07:29.369
I'M SORRY, BUT NO.
NO. I-I --

07:29.369 --> 07:31.572
EXCUSE ME.
I NEED A DIFFERENT DOCTOR.

07:31.572 --> 07:32.623
SARAH...

07:32.623 --> 07:34.124
SHE -- SHE CANNOT TOUCH
MY MOTHER.

07:34.124 --> 07:35.205
IT'S NOT JUST --

07:35.205 --> 07:37.878
I NEED A DIFFERENT DOCTOR
RIGHT NOW.

07:37.878 --> 07:39.079
OKAY. CALM DOWN.
LET'S JUST --

07:39.079 --> 07:40.671
NO!
I WANT ANOTHER DOCTOR!

07:40.671 --> 07:42.042
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM HERE?

07:42.042 --> 07:44.174
SHE CANNOT TOUCH MY MOTHER.
SHE'S A DRUG ADDICT.

07:44.174 --> 07:45.796
I CAN'T HAVE HER OPERATE
ON MY PARENTS.

07:45.796 --> 07:47.177
HOLD IT.
DR. SHEPHERD IS OUR --

07:47.177 --> 07:48.048
IS A JUNKIE.

07:48.048 --> 07:50.180
I MET HER
IN NARCOTICS ANONYMOUS.

07:50.180 --> 07:51.471
SHE'S HOOKED ON OXY.

07:51.471 --> 07:53.013
SHE OVERDOSED
WITH HER BOYFRIEND

07:53.013 --> 07:55.095
AND WOKE UP WITH HIM DEAD
IN BED WITH HER.

07:55.095 --> 07:57.227
I WANT ANOTHER DOCTOR.

07:57.227 --> 07:59.359
NOW!
COME WITH ME.
JUST COME WITH ME, PLEASE.

07:59.359 --> 08:00.601
NO! I'M -- NO, NO!
THIS WAY, PLEASE.

08:00.601 --> 08:01.732
YOU KEEP HER AWAY
FROM THEM!

08:01.732 --> 08:03.153
HUNT, DON'T WORRY.
I'VE GOT THIS.

08:03.153 --> 08:04.064
KEEP HER AWAY FROM THEM!

08:04.064 --> 08:07.067
Owen: FOLLOW ME, MA'AM.
CALM DOWN AND FOLLOW ME.

08:28.178 --> 08:29.089
WHAT WAS THAT?

08:29.089 --> 08:31.682
YOU JUST TOOK
AMELIA'S SURGERY?

08:31.682 --> 08:33.554
WHAT WAS I SUPPOSED TO DO?

08:33.554 --> 08:35.475
TAKE HER SIDE.

08:35.475 --> 08:37.137
SHE WAS BEING ATTACKED.

08:37.137 --> 08:38.809
THE WOMAN HAD IT OUT FOR HER,
MEREDITH.

08:38.809 --> 08:40.400
IF ANYTHING GOES WRONG,
SHE'LL GO BLAMING HER

08:40.400 --> 08:41.902
BECAUSE SHE WAS AN ADDICT.

08:41.902 --> 08:44.314
YOU'RE GONNA GO TALK TO OWEN,
RIGHT, AND CLEAR THIS UP?

08:44.314 --> 08:45.696
YES, I WILL.

08:52.072 --> 08:54.244
I PAGED YOU THREE TIMES.

08:54.244 --> 08:55.576
YEAH,
KEEP YOUR PANTS ON.

08:55.576 --> 08:57.117
I'M CONSULTING
ON THREE BABIES HERE --

08:57.117 --> 08:58.959
I HAVE A MOM WHOSE FETUS IS
BLEEDING INTO HER S.C.T.

08:58.959 --> 09:00.330
SHE NEEDS AN INTRAUTERINE
TRANSFUSION.

09:00.330 --> 09:03.163
IT'S INSERTING A 6-INCH NEEDLE
INTO AN UMBILICAL VEIN

09:03.163 --> 09:05.876
WITHOUT RUPTURING MEMBRANES
OR INDUCING BRADYCARDIA.

09:05.876 --> 09:07.878
I'VE NEVER DONE ONE,
AND HERMAN'S AWOL.

09:07.878 --> 09:09.760
SO, YOU DELIVER.
YOU'LL TAKE THE BABY OUT.

09:09.760 --> 09:11.051
I'LL REPAIR THE S.C.T.
MYSELF.

09:11.051 --> 09:12.382
ALEX,
THE BABY'S 28 WEEKS.

09:12.382 --> 09:14.014
THE WHOLE POINT
IN SEEING HERMAN

09:14.014 --> 09:15.345
WAS TO TRY
AND GET HER TO TERM.

09:15.345 --> 09:16.807
YEAH, IT'D BE GREAT
IF SHE WERE HERE,

09:16.807 --> 09:18.098
BUT I KNOW
HOW TO SAVE THIS KID.

09:18.098 --> 09:20.270
[ SIGHS ]

09:23.023 --> 09:25.065
NICOLE: You've reached the
voicemail of Dr. Nicole Herman.

09:25.065 --> 09:27.107
[ BEEPS ]
HERMAN, ROBBINS AGAIN.

09:27.107 --> 09:29.610
THE JENSEN BABY'S ANEMIC,
AND THE MCA FLOW IS 70.

09:29.610 --> 09:32.993
I WILL GIVE YOU 30 MINUTES,
AND IF I DON'T HEAR FROM YOU,

09:32.993 --> 09:35.115
I'M GONNA DO A C-SECTION
AND RESECT THE S.C.T.

09:35.115 --> 09:36.286
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
OKAY.

09:36.286 --> 09:38.078
I'M GONNA BOOK AN O.R.,

09:38.078 --> 09:39.750
AND CAN YOU BE READY
IN 30 MINUTES IF I NEED YOU?

09:39.750 --> 09:40.791
YEAH.

09:40.791 --> 09:42.122
THAT'S GOOD.
OKAY. THANK YOU.

09:42.122 --> 09:45.045
SHE'S LOSING IT.

09:45.045 --> 09:46.667
YES, SHE IS.

09:46.667 --> 09:47.758
Jo: [ VOMITING ]

09:47.758 --> 09:49.800
LOOK, IT'S YOUR FIRST
SOLO SURGERY.

09:49.800 --> 09:50.971
IT'S A BIG DEAL.

09:50.971 --> 09:52.012
I MEAN,
IF YOU'RE TOO NERVOUS,

09:52.012 --> 09:53.884
I AM MORE THAN HAPPY
TO TAKE IT OFF YOUR HANDS.

09:53.884 --> 09:56.176
I'M NOT NERVOUS.

09:56.176 --> 09:57.928
GREAT. THEN YOU'D BETTER NOT
BE PREGNANT.

09:57.928 --> 09:59.930
BECAUSE IF YOU LET KAREV
THROW A BABY IN THERE,

09:59.930 --> 10:01.101
I WILL NEVER FORGIVE YOU.

10:01.101 --> 10:02.602
I'M NOT PREGNANT,
AND I AM NOT NERVOUS.

10:02.602 --> 10:03.774
I KNOW HOW TO FIX
A HERNIA.

10:03.774 --> 10:05.986
STEP ONE --
MEDIAL DISSECTION.

10:05.986 --> 10:08.108
STEP TWO --
IDENTIFY TRIANGLE OF DOOM,

10:08.108 --> 10:10.070
AVOID THE ILIAC VEIN.

10:10.070 --> 10:11.822
STEP THREE --
PUKE.

10:11.822 --> 10:13.113
BAILEY'S GONNA
EAT YOU ALIVE.

10:13.113 --> 10:14.995
NO, SHE'S NOT,
BECAUSE I'M A BADASS.

10:14.995 --> 10:16.697
STEP THREE --
LATERAL DISSECTION.

10:16.697 --> 10:18.999
STEP FOUR...

10:18.999 --> 10:21.331
IDENTIFY TRIANGLE OF PAIN.

10:21.331 --> 10:23.043
SEE?
GREAT.

10:23.043 --> 10:24.705
I HAVE GOT
THIS PROCEDURE DOWN,

10:24.705 --> 10:27.207
AND I AM NOT AFRAID
OF LITTLE BITTY DR. BAILEY.

10:27.207 --> 10:29.459
[ TOILET FLUSHES ]

10:40.020 --> 10:43.643
THINK YOU COULD TURN THE FAUCET
ON FOR ME, DR. BADASS?

10:43.643 --> 10:46.817
I'D DO IT MYSELF,
ONLY I'M SO LITTLE BITTY.

10:51.862 --> 10:53.734
[ SIGHS ]

10:55.986 --> 10:57.487
[ INDISTINCT WHISPERING ]

10:57.487 --> 10:59.159
WOMAN:
Shh! Here she comes.

10:59.159 --> 11:01.541
That's really scary, the idea
of her operating on someone.

11:01.541 --> 11:03.203
Did you know
she was an addict?

11:03.203 --> 11:04.995
[ INDISTINCT WHISPERING
CONTINUES ]

11:09.379 --> 11:12.462
WOMAN: It must be because
she's Shepherd's sister.

11:12.462 --> 11:15.135
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

11:17.137 --> 11:20.560
SHE JUST SAID IT
IN FRONT OF EVERYONE --

11:20.560 --> 11:22.062
ALL THIS STUFF THAT I SAID
AT MEETINGS ABOUT --

11:22.062 --> 11:23.894
IT'S OKAY.
ARE YOU SOBER?

11:23.894 --> 11:27.147
HOW IS IT OKAY?
EVERYONE IS LOOKING AT ME.

11:27.147 --> 11:28.438
ARE YOU SOBER?

11:28.438 --> 11:30.811
OF COURSE I AM.

11:30.811 --> 11:34.444
DID YOU DISCLOSE YOUR RECOVERY
WHEN YOU WERE HIRED?

11:34.444 --> 11:36.656
I DIDN'T HAVE TO!
DEREK HIRED ME.

11:36.656 --> 11:38.739
HE KNEW.
I ASSUMED PEOPLE KNEW.

11:38.739 --> 11:41.121
AND YOU'VE DONE
NOTHING WRONG.

11:41.121 --> 11:42.412
OKAY? SHE DID.

11:42.412 --> 11:43.994
SHE VIOLATED YOUR PRIVACY.

11:43.994 --> 11:47.167
AND YOU ARE UNDER NO OBLIGATION
TO TELL ANYONE ANYTHING MORE,

11:47.167 --> 11:49.129
UNLESS YOU'VE DONE
SOMETHING

11:49.129 --> 11:52.883
TO COMPROMISE YOUR ABILITY TO DO
YOUR JOB, AND YOU HAVEN'T.

11:52.883 --> 11:55.545
SO YOU DON'T NEED TO SAY
ANYTHING MORE ABOUT IT.

11:55.545 --> 11:57.047
OKAY.

11:57.047 --> 11:59.219
THOSE ARE YOUR RIGHTS.

11:59.219 --> 12:02.262
IT'S THE PAST, AND YOU DON'T
HAVE TO DEFEND IT.

12:04.144 --> 12:06.016
I THOUGHT
I GOT AWAY FROM IT.

12:06.016 --> 12:08.979
COMING HERE,
I THOUGHT...

12:08.979 --> 12:12.062
I THOUGHT
I HAD A CHANCE TO...

12:14.154 --> 12:17.617
BUT YOU NEVER
GET AWAY FROM IT.

12:17.617 --> 12:19.619
NO.

12:19.619 --> 12:22.322
NO, YOU DON'T.

12:25.035 --> 12:27.998
WHAT DO I DO NOW?

12:27.998 --> 12:29.870
YOU JUST STAY ON TRACK.

12:29.870 --> 12:32.873
YOU LOOK AFTER YOURSELF,
DO YOUR JOB.

12:32.873 --> 12:36.336
AND AS SOON AS YOU CAN,
YOU NEED TO GET TO A MEETING.

12:38.588 --> 12:40.380
[ TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS ]

12:40.380 --> 12:42.092
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

12:42.092 --> 12:44.434
Come on, come on, come on.

12:53.153 --> 12:55.986
WELL?

12:55.986 --> 12:58.738
TIME'S UP.
LET'S TAKE THE BABY OUT.

12:58.738 --> 12:59.950
YOU'RE MAKING
THE RIGHT CALL.

12:59.950 --> 13:01.451
[ Rings, beeps ]

13:01.451 --> 13:02.863
HEY, IT'S ROBBINS, AGAIN.

13:02.863 --> 13:04.164
SO YOU'VE LEFT ME
NO CHOICE,

13:04.164 --> 13:06.166
AND FOR ALL I KNOW,
YOU COULD BE DEAD.

13:06.166 --> 13:08.038
SO I'VE MADE MY DECISION
ABOUT YOU.

13:08.038 --> 13:10.210
I AM TELLING CHIEF HUNT AS SOON
AS I GET OUT OF SURGERY.

13:14.254 --> 13:15.465
Is that her?

13:15.465 --> 13:17.177
Yeah, that's her.

13:17.177 --> 13:19.299
[ INDISTINCT WHISPERING ]

13:21.801 --> 13:23.513
DR. SHEPHERD, UM...

13:23.513 --> 13:26.847
COULD WE GO SOMEWHERE PRIVATE
AND TALK?

13:29.139 --> 13:31.311
I'M BUSY RIGHT NOW,
ACTUALLY.

13:31.311 --> 13:32.692
THIS IS IMPORTANT.

13:32.692 --> 13:35.025
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

13:35.025 --> 13:38.198
LISTEN...

13:38.198 --> 13:41.201
IS THERE ANYTHING
YOU WANT TO TELL ME?

13:41.201 --> 13:44.074
TO...CLEAR THIS UP?

13:44.074 --> 13:47.447
I DON'T.

13:47.447 --> 13:49.870
I THINK YOU HEARD
ALL THE FACTS.

13:49.870 --> 13:53.123
WHAT I HEARD WAS A VERY
DISTRAUGHT WOMAN SHOUTING.

13:53.123 --> 13:56.006
AND I THINK THERE IS
ANOTHER SIDE TO THIS STORY.

13:56.006 --> 13:58.218
A WOMAN REQUESTED
ANOTHER DOCTOR,

13:58.218 --> 14:00.420
AND I WAS REMOVED
FROM THE CASE.

14:00.420 --> 14:01.631
THAT IS HER RIGHT.

14:01.631 --> 14:02.923
PEOPLE HAVE RIGHTS.

14:02.923 --> 14:05.225
LISTEN, I AM JUST TRYING
TO HAVE A CONVERSATION.

14:05.225 --> 14:07.137
THAT IS NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS
IF I'M DOING MY JOB.

14:07.137 --> 14:08.268
AM I DOING MY JOB?

14:08.268 --> 14:11.932
AMELIA, I AM TRYING
TO HELP YOU HERE.

14:11.932 --> 14:13.643
I JUST...

14:17.277 --> 14:19.569
I DON'T HAVE TO DISCUSS THIS
WITH YOU.

14:22.112 --> 14:24.444
AND THAT'S YOUR ANSWER?

14:26.446 --> 14:28.368
THAT'S MY RIGHT.

14:31.121 --> 14:32.702
[ SIGHS ]

14:32.702 --> 14:34.664
OKAY.

14:44.134 --> 14:46.176
LET'S CLAMP AND CUT.

14:46.176 --> 14:48.178
AND HERE SHE IS.

14:48.178 --> 14:49.099
I'VE GOT HER.

14:49.099 --> 14:52.472
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S EXTERIORIZE THE UTERUS.

14:52.472 --> 14:54.104
Alex:
STARTING AN UMBILICAL LINE.

14:54.104 --> 14:55.015
HOW'S SHE DOING?

14:55.015 --> 14:57.107
LET'S PRE-OXYGENATE HER
BEFORE WE INTUBATE.

14:57.107 --> 15:00.020
CAN YOU HANDLE THIS?

15:00.020 --> 15:01.441
YOU JUST NEED
TO DELIVER THE PLACENTA

15:01.441 --> 15:02.652
AND THEN CLOSE THE --

15:02.652 --> 15:04.074
I'VE ONLY DONE ABOUT
A MILLION C-SECTIONS.

15:04.074 --> 15:05.285
HOW YOU DOING NOW?
BAD.

15:05.285 --> 15:07.157
O.R. 7 IS WAITING FOR US.

15:07.157 --> 15:09.289
GRAHAM,
I'M GOING WITH THE BABY,

15:09.289 --> 15:11.121
SO JUST COME AND FIND ME
WHEN YOU'RE DONE, ALL RIGHT?

15:11.121 --> 15:14.164
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO!
WE'RE ON THE MOVE!

15:14.164 --> 15:16.746
Maggie: DAMN IT.
THIS LOBE IS TRASHED.

15:16.746 --> 15:17.998
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO DO
A LOBECTOMY.

15:17.998 --> 15:19.629
Stephanie: WE REALLY HAVE TO
TAKE THAT MUCH LUNG?

15:19.629 --> 15:20.961
WE'LL TRY TO SAVE
AS MUCH AS POSSIBLE.

15:20.961 --> 15:22.382
[ MONITORS BEEPING LOUDLY ]
WAIT. WHERE'S THE BLEED?

15:22.382 --> 15:24.174
WHERE'S THE BLEED?
I-I-I CAN'T --
I CAN'T FIND IT.

15:24.174 --> 15:25.385
OKAY.
EVERYTHING OKAY THERE?

15:25.385 --> 15:27.427
ALL RIGHT. HERE'S WHAT YOU DO.
DROP THE SUCTION.
YEAH.

15:27.427 --> 15:29.389
NOW REACH IN THERE
AND GRAB THE HILUM

15:29.389 --> 15:31.681
AND TWIST IT OFF
LIKE A GARDEN HOSE.

15:31.681 --> 15:33.853
JUST SLOW THE FLOW OF BLOOD
UNTIL I CAN FIND --

15:33.853 --> 15:38.018
AH! YES.
THERE WE GO.

15:38.018 --> 15:39.689
HATTIE...

15:39.689 --> 15:41.111
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

15:41.111 --> 15:43.733
THAT WAS, UH --
THAT WAS REALLY COOL.

15:43.733 --> 15:46.156
YOU MAY KEEP GOING,
DR. SHEPHERD, BUT GO EASY.

15:46.156 --> 15:48.568
HATTIE HERE HAS A HOT DATE
WITH HER HUSBAND.

15:48.568 --> 15:50.070
OKAY. GOTCHA.

15:50.070 --> 15:53.373
SINUS FLAP COMING OFF.

15:53.373 --> 15:54.454
YEP,
JUST LIKE IT'S SUPPOSED TO.

15:54.454 --> 15:55.785
GOOD.

15:55.785 --> 15:58.208
BOY OR A GIRL?
WHAT'S THAT?

15:58.208 --> 15:59.379
YOUR BABY.

15:59.379 --> 16:00.750
OH. RIGHT. YES.

16:00.750 --> 16:04.174
UM, ACTUALLY WE HAVE DECIDED
TO BE SURPRISED.

16:04.174 --> 16:05.675
THAT'S A GOOD CALL.

16:05.675 --> 16:08.088
AH, IT'S APRIL'S IDEA.
ACTUALLY, IT'S DRIVING ME CRAZY.

16:08.088 --> 16:09.759
I MEAN,
WHAT WOULD BE THE POINT

16:09.759 --> 16:12.222
OF KNOWING EVERYTHING YOU
POSSIBLY COULD ABOUT YOUR CHILD

16:12.222 --> 16:13.973
WHEN IT'S SO MUCH FUN TO BE
HOPELESSLY UNPREPARED, RIGHT?

16:13.973 --> 16:16.806
YEAH, WE FOUND OUT MY SON
WAS A BOY.

16:16.806 --> 16:18.098
SEE?

16:18.098 --> 16:19.229
YEAH, BUT I DIDN'T KNOW
HE WAS GONNA BE DELIVERED

16:19.229 --> 16:21.651
BY AN INTERN
IN A PITCH-BLACK ROOM

16:21.651 --> 16:24.604
IN THE MIDDLE OF A SUPERSTORM,
BUT SURPRISES HAPPEN.

16:24.604 --> 16:27.657
THAT'S A GOOD STORY,
BUT I FIND NO COMFORT IN IT.

16:27.657 --> 16:29.109
YEAH, WELL, AND THIS.

16:29.109 --> 16:33.113
I'VE BEEN ON THE BENCH
FOR WEEKS, YET HERE I AM,

16:33.113 --> 16:37.247
SAVING A WOMAN'S LIFE
WITHOUT EVEN OPENING HER SKULL.

16:37.247 --> 16:40.040
EMBRACE SURPRISES, AVERY.

16:42.082 --> 16:45.085
Callie: LATERAL INCISION'S DONE.
GOING FOR MEDIAL NOW.

16:45.085 --> 16:47.757
HIS SPLEEN IS SHATTERED. GIVE ME
THE LONGEST KELLY YOU HAVE.

16:47.757 --> 16:50.510
HERE YOU GO.
HE WAS A HUMAN TRAMPOLINE
FOR HIS WIFE.

16:50.510 --> 16:52.932
PRETTY AMAZING.
BETTER THAN BURNING TO DEATH.

16:52.932 --> 16:54.184
I CAN'T IMAGINE.

16:54.184 --> 16:56.766
I CAN IMAGINE THROWING MY WIFE
OUT A WINDOW.

16:56.766 --> 16:58.728
EX-WIFE.

16:58.728 --> 17:01.691
EVERYONE KEEPS SAYING
THAT THINGS WILL GET EASIER,

17:01.691 --> 17:04.854
AND I'M SURE EVERYONE CAN'T BE
WRONG, BUT, MAN, I AM...

17:04.854 --> 17:07.607
[ SIGHS ] I'M REALLY READY
FOR THE EASIER PART.

17:07.607 --> 17:10.029
I THINK DEREK AND I MAY HAVE HIT
THE EASIER PART.

17:10.029 --> 17:11.741
YEAH. YOU MENTIONED.

17:11.741 --> 17:14.204
I DON'T KNOW. WE KEEP CALLING
THESE TIME-OUTS, YOU KNOW?

17:14.204 --> 17:14.994
MM-HMM.

17:14.994 --> 17:16.206
AND THEN WE'RE SO BUSY
TIME-OUTING

17:16.206 --> 17:18.118
THAT WE FORGET
WE'RE EVEN MAD.
HMM.

17:18.118 --> 17:20.420
I DON'T KNOW. HE SEEMS BETTER --
AT HOME, AT LEAST.

17:20.420 --> 17:22.292
I KEEP WAITING
FOR THE OTHER SHOE TO DROP,

17:22.292 --> 17:25.085
BUT MAYBE THERE IS
NO OTHER SHOE.

17:25.085 --> 17:26.506
THERE'S A SHOE.

17:26.506 --> 17:28.968
YOU KNOW
WHAT YOUR TIME-OUTS ARE?

17:28.968 --> 17:30.049
BAND-AIDS.

17:30.049 --> 17:31.171
THEY COVER THE MESS,

17:31.171 --> 17:32.722
THEY STOP THE BLEEDING
FOR A LITTLE WHILE,

17:32.722 --> 17:34.804
BUT YOU'RE JUST IGNORING
THE DAMAGE, AND THEN -- WHKKK!

17:34.804 --> 17:36.226
GOOD TIMES.

17:36.226 --> 17:38.268
TRUST ME.
THERE'S GONNA BE ANOTHER SHOE.

17:40.059 --> 17:42.312
Miranda:
AWFULLY QUIET OVER THERE.

17:42.312 --> 17:44.023
JUST FOCUSED,
DR. BAILEY.

17:44.023 --> 17:47.107
DO YOU THINK YOU SHOULD BE
UPDATING ME ON YOUR PROGRESS?

17:47.107 --> 17:48.318
YEAH.

17:48.318 --> 17:51.321
I, UH, JUST FINISHED
THE MEDIAL DISSECTION

17:51.321 --> 17:53.283
AND IDENTIFIED
THE TRIANGLE OF DOOM,

17:53.283 --> 17:55.615
THEN LATERAL DISSECTION,
TRIANGLE OF PAIN.

17:55.615 --> 17:57.157
ALL THAT'S LEFT
IS THE MESH.

17:57.157 --> 17:59.078
SOUNDS LIKE YOU HAVE
EVERYTHING UNDER CONTROL.

17:59.078 --> 18:01.080
TOTALLY.
TOTALLY UNDER CONTROL.

18:01.080 --> 18:02.622
AND YOU DIDN'T BARF
IN YOUR MASK.

18:02.622 --> 18:04.624
BRAVO.

18:07.006 --> 18:08.798
OKAY, YOU HAVE TO RESECT
REALLY CAREFULLY,

18:08.798 --> 18:09.919
ESPECIALLY THIS PREMATURE.

18:09.919 --> 18:11.090
OH, NO.
THERE'S ANOTHER BLEEDER.

18:11.090 --> 18:13.303
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
DEVASCULARIZE THIS WHOLE THING.

18:13.303 --> 18:14.304
YEP, YEP.
I GOT IT.

18:14.304 --> 18:17.016
THIS IS NICE.
IT'S LIKE OLD TIMES.

18:17.016 --> 18:18.638
YOU HAVEN'T LET ME GET USED TO
THE NEW TIMES.

18:18.638 --> 18:22.432
DR. ROBBINS, DR. MADDOX
HAS ASKED FOR YOU IN O.R. 6.

18:22.432 --> 18:25.064
UGH. GRAHAM...
IT'S A SIMPLE C-SECTION.

18:25.064 --> 18:27.066
I CAN TAKE THIS
IF YOU GOT TO GO.
HE SAYS IT'S URGENT.

18:28.488 --> 18:30.990
PUT THE BLOOD
IN A RAPID INFUSER!
GRAHAM?

18:30.990 --> 18:33.032
THE PLACENTA WAS ADHERED,
AND AS I STARTED TO PULL,
EVERYTHING STARTED BLEEDING!

18:33.032 --> 18:34.694
HOW MANY UNITS
HAS SHE GONE THROUGH?

18:34.694 --> 18:36.035
UH, I DON'T KNOW.
GRAHAM!

18:36.035 --> 18:37.327
TWO, THREE?!
EIGHT.

18:37.327 --> 18:38.738
OH, GOD.

18:38.738 --> 18:40.119
I DID WHAT I WAS SUPPOSED TO!
I PULLED AT THE PLACENTA!

18:40.119 --> 18:43.623
GOWN AND GLOVE ME RIGHT NOW!
DAMN IT, GRAHAM.

18:43.623 --> 18:46.206
IT LOOKS LIKE
PLACENTA PERCRETA.

18:46.206 --> 18:48.127
IT'S PROBABLY INVADING
DEEPER STRUCTURES.

18:48.127 --> 18:49.959
CAN'T YOU SEE THAT?
I MEAN, UGH!

18:49.959 --> 18:52.632
WHY DIDN'T ANYBODY
STOP HIM?!

18:54.013 --> 18:55.255
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN --

18:55.255 --> 18:57.217
CALL HUNT OR ANY TRAUMA SURGEON
THAT'S ON CALL.

18:57.217 --> 18:59.058
ON IT.
GRAHAM, MOVE.

18:59.058 --> 19:00.310
MOVE!

19:06.186 --> 19:08.188
Derek: YOUR MOTHER HAD
A SPINAL-FLUID LEAK.

19:08.188 --> 19:10.480
I WAS ABLE TO STOP IT
WITHOUT OPENING UP HER SKULL.

19:10.480 --> 19:12.532
SHE'S STILL IN SURGERY,

19:12.532 --> 19:15.034
AND WE HOPE TO REPAIR THE DAMAGE
TO HER RIGHT LUNG.

19:15.034 --> 19:17.697
YOUR FATHER HAS
SOME INTERNAL BLEEDING.

19:17.697 --> 19:19.279
WE'LL KNOW MORE SOON.

19:19.279 --> 19:22.542
THANK YOU BOTH SO MUCH.

19:22.542 --> 19:24.834
I DIDN'T WANT
TO DO THAT TO HER...

19:24.834 --> 19:26.996
THAT OTHER DOCTOR.

19:26.996 --> 19:29.249
I'M IN RECOVERY, TOO.

19:29.249 --> 19:31.751
I BROKE AN OATH.

19:31.751 --> 19:35.675
I WANTED -- I WANT TO BE
SUPPORTIVE, BUT...

19:35.675 --> 19:37.427
BUT IT'S MY MOTHER.

19:39.969 --> 19:44.354
WE'LL LET YOU KNOW
WHEN WE KNOW MORE, OKAY?

19:44.354 --> 19:46.145
DEREK, WHAT AM I
LOOKING AT HERE?

19:46.145 --> 19:48.107
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
AMY?

19:48.107 --> 19:50.189
WHAT THAT LADY SAID,
HOW MUCH OF IT IS TRUE?

19:50.189 --> 19:51.861
IS IT ALL TRUE?
SHE'S A DRUG ADDICT?

19:51.861 --> 19:53.943
SHE KILLED HER BOYFRIEND?
SHE'S MY SISTER.

19:53.943 --> 19:55.985
I'M ASKING
BECAUSE I NEED TO KNOW

19:55.985 --> 19:58.778
IF WE WANT HER OUT FRONT
AS NEURO CHIEF.

19:58.778 --> 20:01.241
I'M ASKING YOU
IF YOU THINK

20:01.241 --> 20:04.123
SHE'S THE BEST PERSON
TO BE HEADING THE DEPARTMENT.

20:10.209 --> 20:12.091
OKAY.

20:12.091 --> 20:15.295
I GET IT.
SHE'S YOUR SISTER.

20:15.295 --> 20:16.966
SAY NO MORE.

20:16.966 --> 20:18.097
THANKS.

20:21.180 --> 20:22.602
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

20:22.602 --> 20:24.053
[ CHILD CRYING ]
Shh!

20:30.480 --> 20:31.981
I'M HERE!

20:31.981 --> 20:33.353
PLACENTA PERCRETA INVADING
THE BOWEL AND BLADDER, RIGHT?

20:33.353 --> 20:35.114
I PAGED HUNT.
WHERE'S HUNT?
HE'S BUSY.

20:35.114 --> 20:36.486
WELL, I DIDN'T WANT YOU
TO SEE THIS.

20:36.486 --> 20:37.697
OH, PLEASE.
WHERE DO YOU NEED ME?

20:37.697 --> 20:38.858
GET IN HERE
AND START CLAMPING.

20:38.858 --> 20:40.410
THE ULTRASOUND
DIDN'T DETECT THIS?

20:40.410 --> 20:41.911
NO, EVEN HERMAN
DIDN'T SEE IT.

20:41.911 --> 20:43.122
AND PREGNANT WOMEN HAVE
A HIGHER BLOOD VOLUME,

20:43.122 --> 20:44.494
DISTENDED VESSELS,
THEY BLEED OUT FASTER --

20:44.494 --> 20:46.996
OH, CAN IT, GRAHAM.
OH, NO.

20:46.996 --> 20:48.127
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
WHAT IS IT?

20:48.127 --> 20:49.289
OH, IT EXTENDED
TO HER KIDNEY.

20:49.289 --> 20:50.870
AND THE URETER --
LAP PAD!

20:50.870 --> 20:52.171
KEEP THAT BLOOD COMING!

20:52.171 --> 20:53.963
SHE'S LOSING A LITER
EVERY TWO MINUTES!

20:53.963 --> 20:55.425
GOOD LORD. HOW DO ANY OF US
EVEN HAVE BABIES?

20:55.425 --> 20:56.546
SEE, THAT'S WHY I DIDN'T
WANT YOU IN HERE.

20:56.546 --> 20:57.717
[ SIGHS ]

20:57.717 --> 21:00.970
I SEE NO OTHER INJURIES.
THE BOWEL IS INTACT.

21:00.970 --> 21:03.843
I THINK WE CAN CLOSE.

21:03.843 --> 21:06.306
HOW MUCH LONGER
DO YOU GUYS HAVE?
WHAT'S UP?

21:06.306 --> 21:07.807
I'VE CALLED FOR
AN EMERGENCY BOARD MEETING.

21:07.807 --> 21:09.188
IS THIS ABOUT AMELIA?

21:09.188 --> 21:10.189
IT IS.

21:11.351 --> 21:13.353
DIDN'T DEREK TALK TO YOU?

21:13.353 --> 21:14.814
HE DID.

21:15.565 --> 21:17.487
OWEN. OWEN!

21:19.569 --> 21:21.401
CALLIE.
OTHER SHOE.

21:21.401 --> 21:24.073
WE GOT THIS. GO.
CLOSE FOR ME.

21:24.073 --> 21:25.495
[ DOOR OPENS ]

21:35.625 --> 21:36.716
[ CHILD CRIES ]

21:36.716 --> 21:37.877
Shh!

21:39.088 --> 21:40.299
DID OWEN TALK TO YOU?

21:40.299 --> 21:42.632
I DIDN'T TELL HIM ANYTHING.
I DON'T HAVE ANY--

21:42.632 --> 21:44.053
DID HE TALK TO YOU
ABOUT YOUR JOB?

21:44.053 --> 21:46.976
HE'S SAYING
HE'S GONNA TAKE MY JOB?

21:46.976 --> 21:48.097
YOU'LL TALK TO HIM,
RIGHT?

21:48.097 --> 21:49.098
I DID.
I DID ALREADY.

21:49.098 --> 21:50.770
I THINK I MIGHT HAVE
GIVEN HIM THE IDEA.

21:53.232 --> 21:55.144
OH, NO.
DEREK -- DEREK --

21:55.144 --> 21:56.235
I DIDN'T --
I DIDN'T MEAN TO --
D-DEREK, NO...

21:56.235 --> 21:57.857
I'M SORRY.
I-I WILL FIX IT.

21:57.857 --> 22:00.149
HE WANTS TO GIVE YOU MY JOB,
AND YOU'RE GONNA LET HIM.
NO, I'M NOT.

22:00.149 --> 22:02.402
YOU SON OF A BITCH.
YOU SON OF A BITCH!

22:02.402 --> 22:04.404
YOU KEPT ME HERE!
DON'T.

22:04.404 --> 22:06.075
DON'T. AMY, DON'T.
YOU ASKED ME TO COME.

22:06.075 --> 22:08.498
YOU ASKED ME TO STAY,
WHEN I WAS BUILDING A LIFE --

22:08.498 --> 22:12.081
A NEW LIFE -- A SECOND CHANCE
THAT I HAD GIVEN MYSELF

22:12.081 --> 22:14.083
JUST SO THAT YOU COULD
FEEL BETTER ABOUT LEAVING.

22:14.083 --> 22:16.045
I WAS TRYING TO HELP YOU,
AND I WAS TRYING TO HELP MYSELF.

22:16.045 --> 22:17.126
I WAS JUST TRY--
AND YOU GAVE ME THIS JOB,

22:17.126 --> 22:19.008
AND YOU HAVE ABUSED ME
SINCE THE SECOND I TOOK IT.

22:19.008 --> 22:20.169
BUT THAT IS NOT ENOUGH.

22:20.169 --> 22:21.511
YOU NEED TO DESTROY
MY ENTIRE CAREE--

22:21.511 --> 22:23.593
HOW CAN YOU DO THIS TO ME?
I WILL FI--

22:23.593 --> 22:25.014
TO ME?!
I WILL FIX IT!

22:25.014 --> 22:26.926
HOW CAN YOU DO THIS?!
I WILL TALK TO THEM!

22:26.926 --> 22:29.889
I WILL TALK TO ALL OF THEM,
AND I WILL FIX IT.

22:29.889 --> 22:32.101
YOU'RE MY BROTHER.

22:34.644 --> 22:36.566
[ SIGHS ]

22:37.687 --> 22:39.899
[ SIGHS ]

22:42.982 --> 22:44.243
[ SIGHS ]

22:44.243 --> 22:46.195
I'M LOOKING FOR DEREK SHEPHERD.
HAVE YOU SEEN HIM?

22:46.195 --> 22:47.657
UH, MNH-MNH.

22:47.657 --> 22:48.868
OH, THERE YOU ARE.

22:48.868 --> 22:50.540
WHAT IS GOING ON?
WHAT IS THIS MEETING ABOUT?

22:50.540 --> 22:53.042
THERE'S NOT GONNA BE A MEETING.
I'M GONNA TALK TO HUNT.

22:53.042 --> 22:54.373
HE SAID
HE ALREADY TALKED TO YOU.

22:54.373 --> 22:55.625
HE DID.

22:55.625 --> 22:57.046
WELL, DID YOU SET HIM STRAIGHT
ABOUT AMELIA?

22:57.046 --> 22:59.048
I DIDN'T.

22:59.048 --> 23:00.670
WHAT?

23:00.670 --> 23:03.092
NOT RIGHT NOW, MER.
I CAN'T TALK TO YOU ABOUT THIS.

23:03.092 --> 23:04.714
NOT RIGHT NOW.

23:04.714 --> 23:07.216
DEREK, WHAT DID YOU SAY?

23:07.216 --> 23:09.098
WHAT DID YOU DO?

23:09.098 --> 23:11.310
I JUST FINISHED
MY FIRST SOLO TAPP SURGERY.

23:11.310 --> 23:13.392
ALL RIGHT.
DID YOU THROW UP IN YOUR MASK?

23:13.392 --> 23:15.515
NO. WHY DOES EVERYONE
KEEP ASKING ME THAT?

23:15.515 --> 23:16.516
I NAILED IT.

23:16.516 --> 23:18.017
MEDIAL, LATERAL, PAIN, MESH --
BOOM!

23:18.017 --> 23:20.480
WHAT ABOUT THE TRIANGLE OF DOOM,
THE ILIAC VEIN?

23:20.480 --> 23:22.321
WHAT ABOUT IT?
WELL, YOU SKIPPED IT.

23:22.321 --> 23:23.983
NO, I DIDN'T.

23:23.983 --> 23:25.575
JO, YOU DIDN'T SAY IT.

23:25.575 --> 23:27.987
BUT I DID IT.

23:27.987 --> 23:31.160
IN THERE.
I-I DIDN'T SKIP IT IN THERE.

23:31.160 --> 23:32.662
IN THERE, I...

23:32.662 --> 23:34.293
I DID IT, RIGHT?

23:34.293 --> 23:36.035
ARE YOU ASKING ME?

23:38.247 --> 23:40.089
MEDIUM CLIP.
GOT IT.

23:40.089 --> 23:41.420
3-0 SILK.
HANG ANOTHER UNIT.

23:41.420 --> 23:43.543
SHE'S GONE THROUGH 100 UNITS
OF BLOOD PRODUCTS.

23:43.543 --> 23:45.004
Woman: DR. ROBBINS,
DR. KAREV IS ASKING TO SEE YOU.

23:45.004 --> 23:46.175
OH, HER BABY.

23:46.175 --> 23:47.547
DID HE SAY WHAT'S WRONG?

23:47.547 --> 23:48.758
JUST THAT HE NEEDED YOU.

23:48.758 --> 23:49.929
DAMN.
GO.

23:49.929 --> 23:51.851
NO, I CAN'T LEAVE
THIS WOMAN.
I GOT HER.

23:51.851 --> 23:53.182
MAKE SURE HER BABY'S OKAY.

23:53.182 --> 23:54.934
[ MONITORS BEEPING ]

23:57.056 --> 23:58.898
OHH.
SORRY!

24:02.652 --> 24:05.775
W-WHAT HAPPENED?
WHERE'S DR. KAREV?!

24:07.907 --> 24:09.368
WHAT IS IT?
WHAT HAPPENED?

24:09.368 --> 24:11.030
OH, I FINISHED.
IT WENT WELL.

24:11.030 --> 24:12.331
YOU WERE ALL IN A TWIST
ABOUT THIS KID,

24:12.331 --> 24:13.833
SO I THOUGHT YOU'D WANT
TO UPDATE THE DAD WITH ME.

24:13.833 --> 24:15.414
OH, GOD.
ALEX, NO, HIS WIFE IS --

24:15.414 --> 24:16.746
IS THE BABY OKAY?

24:16.746 --> 24:19.128
YES.
UH, THE SURGERY WENT WELL.

24:19.128 --> 24:20.419
HER VITALS ARE GOOD.

24:20.419 --> 24:23.172
SHE'LL LIKELY NEED TO STAY
IN THE NICU FOR A WHILE,

24:23.172 --> 24:24.383
BUT SHE'S LOOKING GOOD.

24:24.383 --> 24:25.585
HAS EMILY SEEN HER?

24:25.585 --> 24:27.176
SHE'S STILL IN SURGERY.

24:27.176 --> 24:28.508
UM, THERE WERE SOME
COMPLICATIONS

24:28.508 --> 24:29.549
DURING HER C-SECTION.

24:29.549 --> 24:30.890
WAIT,
SHE'S STILL IN SURGERY?

24:30.890 --> 24:32.852
WE'RE DOING
EVERYTHING THAT WE CAN.

24:32.852 --> 24:34.013
I-I HAVE TO GO BACK.

24:34.013 --> 24:35.264
EVERYTHING YOU CAN?

24:35.264 --> 24:36.856
HOW SERIOUS IS THIS?

24:36.856 --> 24:38.978
SHE LOST A LOT OF BLOOD.

24:38.978 --> 24:41.731
WHERE'S DR. HERMAN?
DR. HERMAN HAD A PLAN.

24:41.731 --> 24:43.022
NOW YOU'VE GOT MY BABY
IN CRITICAL CARE,

24:43.022 --> 24:44.524
AND MY WIFE
IS BLEEDING TO DEATH!

24:44.524 --> 24:46.155
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHO YOU ARE.

24:46.155 --> 24:47.026
I HAVE TO GO BACK.

24:50.069 --> 24:52.742
WHERE THE HELL
IS OUR DOCTOR?!

25:02.041 --> 25:04.544
April:
[ Echoing ] TIME OF DEATH...

25:04.544 --> 25:06.626
18:22.

25:27.236 --> 25:28.648
IT WAS JUST
A MISUNDERSTANDING WITH OWEN.

25:28.648 --> 25:30.279
HE'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.
HE SAID HE WOULD.

25:30.279 --> 25:32.201
HE DID THIS, MEREDITH.

25:32.201 --> 25:34.453
WHY SHOULD I BELIEVE THAT?

25:34.453 --> 25:35.615
WHY DO YOU BELIEVE IT?

25:35.615 --> 25:37.116
BECAUSE HE'S YOUR BROTHER.

25:37.116 --> 25:38.998
THAT'S WHY HE CAN DO IT.

25:38.998 --> 25:40.870
IT'S WHY HE COULD
STEAL MY TOYS

25:40.870 --> 25:42.752
AND PULL MY HAIR
AND CALL ME NAMES.

25:42.752 --> 25:44.503
IT'S BECAUSE I'M FAMILY.

25:44.503 --> 25:48.547
IT'S WHY HE THINKS
HE CAN GET AWAY WITH THIS.

25:48.547 --> 25:49.929
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:49.929 --> 25:51.470
YOU DON'T GET IT.

25:51.470 --> 25:53.512
NO. I DON'T.

25:53.512 --> 25:56.095
I WAS RAISED
AS AN ONLY CHILD.

25:56.095 --> 25:59.348
AND I'M HISTORICALLY LOUSY
AT BEING A SISTER.

25:59.348 --> 26:02.311
YOU'RE HERE RIGHT NOW.

26:02.311 --> 26:03.983
[ SIGHS ]

26:03.983 --> 26:06.485
THAT'S GOOD ENOUGH.

26:08.317 --> 26:10.319
YOU DON'T REMEMBER?

26:10.319 --> 26:12.151
NO, I --
OF COURSE I REMEMBER.

26:12.151 --> 26:14.323
I-I JUST WANTED
TO DOUBLE-CHECK WITH YOU,

26:14.323 --> 26:15.534
YOU KNOW, TO BE SAFE.

26:15.534 --> 26:19.118
MY LATERAL DISSECTION,
IT LOOKED GOOD, RIGHT?

26:19.118 --> 26:20.539
I-I DON'T THINK I WENT ANYWHERE
NEAR THE ILIAC VEIN.

26:20.539 --> 26:21.791
YOU DON'T THINK --

26:21.791 --> 26:23.913
WILSON, EITHER YOU HIT
THE WOMAN'S ILIAC VEIN

26:23.913 --> 26:25.004
OR YOU DIDN'T.

26:25.004 --> 26:26.045
WHICH ONE IS IT?

26:28.087 --> 26:29.128
I DON'T...

26:29.128 --> 26:31.130
SO, WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

26:31.130 --> 26:33.633
WE RUN A C.T. --

26:33.633 --> 26:35.214
NO. I RUN A C.T.

26:35.214 --> 26:36.215
YOU?

26:36.215 --> 26:37.426
YOU JUST STAND HERE
AND PRAY

26:37.426 --> 26:40.850
THAT YOUR PATIENT ISN'T BLEEDING
TO DEATH RIGHT NOW.

26:43.062 --> 26:44.563
[ DOOR OPENS ]

26:44.563 --> 26:46.185
Owen: SO ROBBINS IS TIED UP.
SHOULD WE WAIT?

26:46.185 --> 26:47.817
NO, YEAH,
WE SHOULD GET STARTED.

26:47.817 --> 26:49.989
NO, NO, NO.
WELL, DEREK, WE JUST NEED
TO FIGURE OUT --

26:49.989 --> 26:52.111
I KNOW YOU'RE TRYING TO FIGURE
OUT WHAT'S GOING ON.

26:52.111 --> 26:56.906
I KNOW YOU'VE HEARD SOME STORIES
ABOUT AMELIA.

26:56.906 --> 26:59.659
I LET YOU BELIEVE SOMETHING.
I LET YOU BELIEVE THAT, UH --

26:59.659 --> 27:03.162
SHEPHERD, YOU WERE PRETTY CLEAR
WHEN WE SPOKE, SO --

27:03.162 --> 27:05.835
SHE'S IN RECOVERY.

27:05.835 --> 27:07.376
SHE WORKS REALLY HARD AT IT.

27:07.376 --> 27:10.299
SHE'S BEEN SUCCESSFUL
IN RECOVERY, AND...

27:10.299 --> 27:12.461
[ SIGHS ]

27:12.461 --> 27:14.093
[ GUNSHOT ]

27:17.016 --> 27:19.518
THIS HOSPITAL SHOULD HAVE
PROTECTED HER.

27:19.518 --> 27:22.021
THIS WOMAN
SHOULD HAVE PROTECTED HER.

27:22.021 --> 27:23.102
AND...

27:25.815 --> 27:28.107
[ BELL JINGLES ]

27:29.899 --> 27:34.984
MORE IMPORTANTLY,
I SHOULD HAVE PROTECTED HER.

27:34.984 --> 27:38.277
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

27:41.450 --> 27:42.621
I DIDN'T.

27:42.621 --> 27:44.543
[ GUN COCKS ]

27:47.246 --> 27:50.379
AND I DIDN'T
BECAUSE I WANTED HER JOB.

27:52.091 --> 27:53.883
I WANTED MY OLD JOB BACK.

27:53.883 --> 27:56.055
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

28:00.139 --> 28:02.141
SO NOW WE'RE HERE.

28:09.068 --> 28:10.399
MY FAULT.

28:13.943 --> 28:16.075
[ SIGHS ]

28:17.737 --> 28:21.030
DEREK,
WHY DID YOU EVEN...?

28:25.084 --> 28:28.958
SHE SHOULD STAY WHERE SHE IS,
OWEN.

28:28.958 --> 28:31.090
SHE CAN DO THE JOB.

28:31.090 --> 28:33.172
SHE IS DOING THE JOB.

28:35.424 --> 28:39.508
I COULDN'T DO IT ANY BETTER.

28:43.973 --> 28:45.684
HOW'S HIS BABY?
IS THERE ANY CHANGE?

28:45.684 --> 28:47.726
NO. SHE'S GOOD. SHE'S STABLE.
LET ME DO IT.

28:47.726 --> 28:49.849
NO, I HAVE TO TELL HIM.

28:49.849 --> 28:51.230
HOW? HOW, ALEX?

28:51.230 --> 28:54.063
HOW DO I TELL HIM
THAT HIS WIFE IS DEAD?

28:54.063 --> 28:55.985
WHERE THE HELL IS HERMAN?
SHE SHOULD HAVE BEEN HERE.

28:55.985 --> 28:57.486
THAT'S NOT HELPING!
I WAS HERE.

28:57.486 --> 28:59.318
EMILY WAS MY RESPONSIBILITY,
AND I LOST HER.

28:59.318 --> 29:02.121
SO LET ME DO IT.

29:08.417 --> 29:11.250
PLACENTA PERCRETA
IS VERY DIFFICULT TO DIAGNOSE,

29:11.250 --> 29:15.334
AND IN CASES AS SEVERE
AS EMILY'S, IT'S USUALLY...

29:15.334 --> 29:16.796
INSURMOUNTABLE.

29:16.796 --> 29:18.507
IF YOUR BABY HAD
COME TO TERM,

29:18.507 --> 29:20.429
IT'S LIKELY
EMILY WOULD HAVE DIED.

29:20.429 --> 29:22.341
NO.

29:22.341 --> 29:25.724
COREY, THIS IS WHAT
YOU HAVE TO UNDERSTAND.

29:25.724 --> 29:27.937
IF I'D DONE THE SURGERY
WE'D PLANNED,

29:27.937 --> 29:29.768
IT'S LIKELY THAT,
DOWN THE LINE,

29:29.768 --> 29:33.062
WE WOULD HAVE LOST EMILY
AND YOUR DAUGHTER.

29:33.062 --> 29:36.025
DR. ROBBINS DID EVERYTHING
WITHIN HER POWER FOR YOUR WIFE.

29:36.025 --> 29:39.108
BUT SHE SAVED
YOUR BABY'S LIFE.

29:39.108 --> 29:42.281
YOUR BABY IS ALIVE
BECAUSE OF HER.

29:45.574 --> 29:47.666
I'M NOT SURE
WHAT THAT WAS ABOUT,

29:47.666 --> 29:49.668
BUT IT DOESN'T CHANGE
ANYTHING.

29:49.668 --> 29:51.871
OKAY? I CAN'T DO IT.
I WON'T DO IT.

29:51.871 --> 29:53.082
YOU -- YOU ABANDONED ME.

29:53.082 --> 29:55.004
YOU -- YOU LEFT ME NO CHOICE
BUT TO TAKE THAT BABY.

29:55.004 --> 29:57.336
YOU MADE ME --
[ COUGHING, VOMITING ]

30:03.422 --> 30:06.015
ARE --
[ TOILET FLUSHES ]

30:09.018 --> 30:11.140
[ GROANS ]

30:11.140 --> 30:13.482
GO AHEAD.
FINISH YOUR THING.

30:13.482 --> 30:15.144
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

30:15.144 --> 30:16.485
WELL, I --
[ COUGHS ]

30:16.485 --> 30:17.566
I, UM...

30:17.566 --> 30:20.489
OH, NO, NO.
GO ON. GET IT OUT.

30:20.489 --> 30:23.152
[ SIGHS ]

30:23.152 --> 30:24.283
THANK YOU.

30:28.077 --> 30:29.248
WHAT?

30:29.248 --> 30:31.330
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

30:31.330 --> 30:34.163
YESTERDAY,
MY DOCTORS DECIDED

30:34.163 --> 30:39.088
I NEED SOME AGGRESSIVE
RADIATION THERAPY IMMEDIATELY,

30:39.088 --> 30:41.840
SO THAT'S
WHERE I WAS TODAY.

30:41.840 --> 30:43.012
IT JUST...

30:43.012 --> 30:46.675
HIT ME A LITTLE HARDER
THAN I EXPECTED.

30:46.675 --> 30:50.179
EVERYTHING I SAID TO THAT MAN
WAS TRUE.

30:50.179 --> 30:52.892
YOU SAVED A BABY
THAT WE WOULD HAVE LOST.

30:52.892 --> 30:54.813
I WATCHED YOU.

30:54.813 --> 30:56.605
I LOGGED IN
TO THE HOSPITAL INTERFACE.

30:56.605 --> 30:59.398
I MONITORED YOUR PROGRESS
ALL DAY.

30:59.398 --> 31:01.320
[ SNIFFLES ]

31:01.320 --> 31:02.741
YOU MADE THE RIGHT CALL.

31:02.741 --> 31:04.483
YOU MADE
ALL THE RIGHT CALLS.

31:04.483 --> 31:06.155
THAT'S NOT --
IF -- IF YOU HAD BEEN HERE,

31:06.155 --> 31:08.247
YOU WOULD'VE --
MNH-MNH. NO.

31:08.247 --> 31:10.079
THE ONLY THING
I COULD'VE DONE

31:10.079 --> 31:12.451
IS PERFORM
AN INTRAUTERINE TRANSFUSION,

31:12.451 --> 31:14.543
TRY TO KEEP THE BABY IN
A LITTLE LONGER,

31:14.543 --> 31:16.996
GET HER CLOSER TO TERM.

31:16.996 --> 31:18.998
AND MAYBE -- MAYBE --

31:18.998 --> 31:23.002
WE COULD HAVE DETECTED
THE PERCRETA EARLIER,

31:23.002 --> 31:25.264
BUT IT DOESN'T MEAN WE COULD'VE
DONE ANYTHING FOR HER

31:25.264 --> 31:26.635
THAT YOU DIDN'T DO.

31:26.635 --> 31:30.009
I WANT TO KNOW HOW TO DO IT,
THE INTRAUTERINE TRANSFUSION.

31:30.009 --> 31:33.142
'CAUSE IF THERE'S A CHANCE
THAT I COULD'VE SAVED THAT MOM,

31:33.142 --> 31:34.934
THEN I NEED TO KNOW HOW.

31:34.934 --> 31:36.105
FOR THE NEXT TIME.

31:36.105 --> 31:38.938
I CAN SHOW YOU TOMORROW.

31:40.479 --> 31:43.983
UNLESS YOU'RE PLANNING TO HAVE
A CONVERSATION WITH CHIEF HUNT.

31:53.912 --> 31:55.034
OKAY.

31:55.034 --> 31:56.996
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

31:56.996 --> 31:58.747
GO HOME.

32:00.249 --> 32:01.800
[ DOOR OPENS ]

32:06.885 --> 32:08.177
IT'S GONNA BE FINE.

32:08.177 --> 32:10.679
HEY, I'M GONNA BE HERE
WITH YOU, OKAY?

32:10.679 --> 32:12.761
[ DOOR OPENS ]

32:12.761 --> 32:14.553
EDWARDS, OUT.

32:14.553 --> 32:16.355
YES, MA'AM.

32:17.766 --> 32:19.728
[ SIGHS ]

32:19.728 --> 32:21.060
HOW WAS THE C.T.?

32:21.060 --> 32:22.982
SHE NEVER MADE IT
TO C.T.

32:22.982 --> 32:24.733
WAIT --

32:24.733 --> 32:26.905
THIS WAS YOUR SURGERY,
WILSON.

32:26.905 --> 32:29.618
I'M GONNA NEED YOU
TO TALK TO THE FAMILY.

32:29.618 --> 32:32.201
OH, MY GOD.

32:32.201 --> 32:33.332
SHE'S DEAD?

32:33.332 --> 32:35.204
SHE'S DEAD?
OH, MY GOD.
I NEVER SAID THAT.

32:35.204 --> 32:36.955
I-I REMEMBER DOING
EVERYTHING CORRECTLY.
WILSON.

32:36.955 --> 32:38.077
I EVEN -- I EVEN --

32:38.077 --> 32:39.628
SHE'S FINE!

32:39.628 --> 32:40.839
WHAT?

32:40.839 --> 32:42.251
I DIDN'T SAY
SHE WAS DEAD.

32:42.251 --> 32:44.963
I SAID
SHE NEVER MADE IT TO C.T.

32:44.963 --> 32:47.546
YOU'RE --
YOU'RE SCREWING WITH ME.

32:47.546 --> 32:50.009
I DIDN'T TAKE HER
TO C.T.

32:50.009 --> 32:53.932
BECAUSE I SAW YOU DO IT
IN THE O.R., DR. BADASS.

32:53.932 --> 32:55.764
OH, MY GOD.

32:55.764 --> 32:58.727
OH, MY GOD!
YOU HAVE A PROBLEM!

32:58.727 --> 33:00.189
NO, YOU DO.

33:00.189 --> 33:02.771
YOU SECOND-GUESS YOURSELF.

33:02.771 --> 33:05.364
THIS WAS THE FIRST
IN A CAREER FULL OF SURGERIES

33:05.364 --> 33:06.775
YOU WILL BE DOING ALONE.

33:06.775 --> 33:07.986
BEFORE TOO LONG,

33:07.986 --> 33:10.989
THERE WON'T BE ANYONE
TO CATCH YOU WHEN YOU FALL.

33:10.989 --> 33:12.661
YOUR PATIENTS
NEED TO TRUST

33:12.661 --> 33:14.913
THAT WHEN YOU TAKE THEM
INTO SURGERY,

33:14.913 --> 33:16.375
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

33:16.375 --> 33:18.747
NOW, HOW CAN YOU EXPECT THEM
TO DO THAT

33:18.747 --> 33:21.080
IF YOU DON'T EVEN
TRUST YOURSELF?

33:21.080 --> 33:22.381
YOU ARE SO MEAN.

33:22.381 --> 33:24.833
I AM, INDEED.

33:24.833 --> 33:27.046
TELL ALL YOUR
LITTLE BITTY FRIENDS.

33:33.011 --> 33:35.134
[ SIGHS ] HEY.

33:35.134 --> 33:38.137
I HEARD ABOUT YOUR PATIENT.
YOU OKAY?

33:38.137 --> 33:41.060
THERE WAS SO MUCH BLOOD,
JACKSON.

33:41.060 --> 33:43.902
I MEAN, I KNOW WE SEE IT
ALL THE TIME, BUT...

33:43.902 --> 33:45.023
YEAH.

33:45.023 --> 33:46.985
I JUST -- I DIDN'T THINK
IT WAS GONNA STOP.

33:46.985 --> 33:50.199
AND I KNOW
IT CAN BE SCARY.

33:50.199 --> 33:55.704
BUT YOU AND OUR BABY
ARE JUST FINE.

33:55.704 --> 33:58.657
SO DO NOT WORRY, OKAY?

33:58.657 --> 34:01.120
I'M NOT WORRIED.

34:01.120 --> 34:02.961
ARE YOU WORRIED?

34:02.961 --> 34:06.165
ALL THE TIME.

34:06.165 --> 34:08.837
HOW CAN YOU NOT BE?

34:12.010 --> 34:15.174
YOU KNOW HOW.

34:15.174 --> 34:16.385
RIGHT.

34:16.385 --> 34:20.099
IT'S ALL IN GOD'S HANDS.

34:20.099 --> 34:21.140
YEAH.

34:21.140 --> 34:24.683
GOD, I DON'T KNOW
HOW YOU CAN DO THAT --

34:24.683 --> 34:28.357
JUST WRITE OFF ALL
THE UNANSWERED QUESTIONS.

34:28.357 --> 34:31.190
WE DON'T GET TO KNOW
THE ANSWERS.

34:31.190 --> 34:32.991
THAT'S YOUR ANSWER.

34:32.991 --> 34:36.955
I DON'T KNOW WHY THAT WOMAN
HAD TO DIE TONIGHT.

34:36.955 --> 34:39.658
SHE EXSANGUINATED.
THAT'S WHY.

34:39.658 --> 34:41.370
YEAH, OKAY. BUT WHY?

34:41.370 --> 34:45.164
BECAUSE ALL OF IT JUST...

34:45.164 --> 34:48.547
ALL OF IT JUST HAPPENED.

34:50.879 --> 34:53.212
YOU'RE REALLY COMFORTABLE
WITH THAT ANSWER?

34:53.212 --> 34:54.633
HMM?

34:54.633 --> 34:56.385
YEAH.

34:56.385 --> 34:58.217
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:58.217 --> 35:00.559
SEE, I DON'T KNOW
HOW YOU DO THAT.

35:00.559 --> 35:04.062
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

35:04.062 --> 35:07.105
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

35:13.822 --> 35:14.823
IS THAT YOU?

35:14.823 --> 35:16.825
[ SIGHS ]
HOW'S HATTIE?

35:16.825 --> 35:18.197
THORACOTOMY.

35:18.197 --> 35:21.500
I HAD TO RESECT
HER ENTIRE RIGHT LOWER LOBE.

35:21.500 --> 35:24.293
SHE'S GONNA NEED
RIB STABILIZATION.

35:24.293 --> 35:27.045
NORRIS, TOO.
EX-LAP, AVULSED SPLEEN.

35:27.045 --> 35:29.047
TORRES DID A FASCIOTOMY
ON HIS RIGHT LEG.

35:29.047 --> 35:31.009
I THINK IT'S GONNA BE OKAY,
THOUGH.

35:31.009 --> 35:33.422
WE'LL SEE IF HER LUNGS
DON'T SHUT DOWN OVERNIGHT.

35:33.422 --> 35:35.634
WE GAVE THEM
THE BEST CHANCE WE COULD.

35:35.634 --> 35:38.637
YEAH. WE'LL SEE.

35:38.637 --> 35:40.809
WE'LL SEE.

35:40.809 --> 35:42.601
AGAIN,
ABOUT LAST NIGHT --

35:42.601 --> 35:43.762
WOULD YOU LET IT GO?
I'M NOT MAD.

35:44.973 --> 35:46.935
WELL, YOU SOUND LIKE SOMEONE
WHO'S MAD.

35:46.935 --> 35:48.026
OF COURSE I'M MAD.

35:48.026 --> 35:50.359
YOU INVITED ME TO DINNER,

35:50.359 --> 35:52.481
AND THEN DIDN'T COME TO
THE DINNER -- AT YOUR OWN HOUSE!

35:52.481 --> 35:54.233
I KNOW.
I TOLD DEREK IT WAS A BAD IDEA.

35:54.233 --> 35:56.195
YOU DIDN'T WANT
TO TALK TO RICHARD.

35:56.195 --> 36:00.078
I WANTED TO HAVE DINNER --
WITH PEOPLE AND CONVERSATION.

36:00.078 --> 36:02.160
I DON'T KNOW ANYONE HERE.

36:02.160 --> 36:03.872
I HAVE NO FRIENDS.

36:03.872 --> 36:05.374
I DO NOTHING AT NIGHT.

36:05.374 --> 36:07.496
I GO
TO THE GROCERY STORE,

36:07.496 --> 36:10.669
AND I BUY SAD
SINGLE-SERVING PACKETS OF FOOD

36:10.669 --> 36:13.001
FOR SAD PEOPLE
WHO EAT ALONE.

36:13.001 --> 36:15.554
I WAS REALLY EXCITED
FOR POT ROAST.

36:15.554 --> 36:16.845
AND PEOPLE!

36:16.845 --> 36:20.008
I CHANGED MY OUTFIT
FOUR TIMES.

36:20.008 --> 36:22.351
AND, NO, I-I DIDN'T WANT
TO TALK TO WEBBER,

36:22.351 --> 36:24.853
BUT THAT WASN'T GONNA STOP ME
FROM COMING,

36:24.853 --> 36:27.516
BECAUSE I'M REALLY SICK
OF TALKING BACK TO MY TV,

36:27.516 --> 36:29.147
AND I'M SCARED
I'M GONNA GET A CAT.

36:29.147 --> 36:30.649
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:30.649 --> 36:33.151
AND I WAS REALLY EXCITED

36:33.151 --> 36:37.025
THAT SOMEONE
HAD INVITED ME TO DINNER.

36:37.025 --> 36:39.368
SO, YEAH, I'M PRETTY MAD.

36:39.368 --> 36:42.120
[ RINGTONE PLAYS ]

36:42.120 --> 36:43.372
HATTIE'S AWAKE.

36:45.083 --> 36:46.415
WHAT?

36:46.415 --> 36:48.957
WHAT HAPPENED?

36:48.957 --> 36:52.961
MOM, THERE WAS A FIRE
IN YOUR APARTMENT.

36:52.961 --> 36:56.174
YOU'VE HAD SURGERY,
BUT YOU'RE DOING WELL.

36:56.174 --> 36:58.337
YOUR HUSBAND
SAVED YOUR LIFE.

36:58.337 --> 37:01.930
HE PICKED YOU UP AND JUMPED OUT
A WINDOW WITH YOU.

37:01.930 --> 37:03.392
WELL, THAT WAS STUPID.

37:03.392 --> 37:05.394
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

37:06.975 --> 37:12.110
OH, NORRIS,
YOU SAVED MY LIFE.

37:12.110 --> 37:15.153
I NEARLY KILLED YOU.

37:15.153 --> 37:20.068
BUT THAT DOCTOR,
SHE PROMISED.

37:20.068 --> 37:22.951
WHERE IS SHE,
THAT WOMAN DOCTOR?

37:22.951 --> 37:24.993
OH, DR. SHEPHERD.

37:24.993 --> 37:31.169
SHE PROMISED THEY'D SAVE YOU,
AND SHE WAS RIGHT.

37:31.169 --> 37:33.292
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:45.304 --> 37:46.685
ARE YOU BUSY TONIGHT?

37:46.685 --> 37:49.558
OH, WELL, I WAS GOING TO
CATCH UP ON SOME READING,

37:49.558 --> 37:52.190
SOME MEDICAL JOURNALS,
BUT...

37:52.190 --> 37:55.193
OH, ACTUALLY, NO.

37:55.193 --> 37:58.026
NO, I AM, UM --
I'M NOT BUSY.

37:58.026 --> 37:59.157
WHY?

37:59.157 --> 38:02.070
♪ YEAH, I'M COOL ♪

38:02.070 --> 38:05.033
♪ EVERYTHING SEEMS TO BE FINE ♪

38:05.033 --> 38:07.366
THIS WAS ELLIS' HOUSE.

38:07.366 --> 38:09.207
♪ BUT I DON'T FEEL
THE SAME INSIDE ♪

38:09.207 --> 38:11.119
THIS IS WHERE YOU GREW UP.

38:11.119 --> 38:13.502
IT WAS NICER
BEFORE ALEX TRASHED IT.

38:13.502 --> 38:15.714
OH, SHUT UP.
IT SMELLED LIKE BOOKS.

38:15.714 --> 38:17.916
[ LAUGHTER ]
WELL, IT SMELLED A LOT BETTER
WHEN I LIVED HERE.

38:17.916 --> 38:19.297
NOW IT JUST SMELLS
LIKE KAREV.

38:19.297 --> 38:21.510
[ LAUGHING ]
WAIT. YOU LIVED HERE, TOO?

38:21.510 --> 38:23.301
Alex and Meredith:
EVERYBODY LIVED HERE.

38:23.301 --> 38:25.263
I PRACTICALLY LIVED HERE
WITH GEORGE, RIGHT?

38:25.263 --> 38:26.845
GEORGE WAS
MY EX-HUSBAND.

38:26.845 --> 38:28.096
HE WAS IN
THEIR RESIDENT CLASS.

38:28.096 --> 38:29.518
O'MALLEY.

38:29.518 --> 38:32.060
O'MALLEY.

38:32.060 --> 38:33.812
I'M SORRY.
YOUR HUSBAND?

38:33.812 --> 38:35.143
YEAH,
SHE DOES DUDES, TOO.

38:35.143 --> 38:36.435
TRUE.
I DID HIM ONCE.

38:36.435 --> 38:38.026
TRUE.
[ LAUGHING ]

38:38.026 --> 38:39.488
SHE DID.

38:39.488 --> 38:41.109
I DIDN'T DO HIM.

38:41.109 --> 38:43.071
I DID DO GEORGE, THOUGH --
ONCE.

38:43.071 --> 38:44.443
OH-HO-HO!
YEAH, YEAH.

38:44.443 --> 38:45.784
OH, GOD.
YEAH, YEAH.

38:45.784 --> 38:47.285
WE'RE ALL RELATED
THROUGH SEX.

38:47.285 --> 38:49.368
[ LAUGHS ]
WE ALL HAVE SEXUAL RELATIONS.

38:49.368 --> 38:51.039
THAT IS HORRIBLY WEIRD.

38:51.039 --> 38:53.372
♪ I'M NOT AFRAID
TO USE THE PHONE ♪
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

38:53.372 --> 38:56.084
♪ 'CAUSE I DON'T
HAVE TO BE ALONE ♪

38:56.084 --> 38:58.216
[ LAUGHTER ]
♪ NO, I'LL NEVER BE SCARED ♪

38:58.216 --> 39:02.801
♪ AND, OH, SO I FIND MYSELF
AT HOME ♪

39:02.801 --> 39:04.383
♪ AND THAT'S ALL RIGHT ♪

39:04.383 --> 39:06.675
HI.

39:06.675 --> 39:09.177
Meredith: IT'S HARD TO GIVE
SECOND CHANCES.

39:09.177 --> 39:10.729
♪ TO GET THAT GOOD FEELING ♪

39:10.729 --> 39:13.732
I PROBABLY SHOULD'VE CALLED
FIRST, BUT...

39:13.732 --> 39:15.183
SOMEONE TOLD ME TO GO HOME,

39:15.183 --> 39:17.476
AND I WASN'T REALLY SURE
WHERE I SHOULD GO.

39:17.476 --> 39:21.069
SEE?
EVERYONE LIVES HERE.

39:21.069 --> 39:24.693
BEER'S IN THE FRIDGE.
HARD STUFF'S ON THE COUNTER.

39:24.693 --> 39:26.485
THANK YOU.

39:26.485 --> 39:28.487
IT'S EVEN HARDER
TO ASK FOR THEM.

39:28.487 --> 39:31.910
♪ I'M ALL GOOD,
I'LL BE ON MY WAY ♪

39:31.910 --> 39:33.452
♪ AND I FIND MYSELF AT HOME ♪

39:33.452 --> 39:38.086
A CHANCE TO DO IT AGAIN,
KNOWING WHAT YOU KNOW NOW...

39:38.086 --> 39:40.168
♪ I'M HOME,
NO, I NEVER LOOK BACK ♪

39:40.168 --> 39:41.460
WHAT YOU'VE LEARNED...

39:41.460 --> 39:44.002
♪ HOLD ON TO WHAT I HAVE ♪

39:44.002 --> 39:47.055
...A CHANCE TO DO IT
COMPLETELY DIFFERENTLY...

39:47.055 --> 39:49.598
♪ 'CAUSE I DON'T
HAVE TO BE ALONE ♪

39:49.598 --> 39:51.309
♪ NO, I'LL NEVER BE SCARED ♪

39:51.309 --> 39:55.273
♪ AND, OH,
WHEN I FIND MYSELF AT HOME ♪

39:56.435 --> 39:58.977
Derek: YOU OKAY?

40:01.570 --> 40:02.981
I WAS AT A MEETING.

40:05.073 --> 40:07.155
I'M MOVING OUT.

40:07.155 --> 40:08.907
TOMORROW.

40:08.907 --> 40:10.078
I'M SORRY.

40:10.078 --> 40:11.660
I'M JUST SO SORRY.

40:11.660 --> 40:14.663
DON'T, DEREK.
DON'T EVEN BOTHER.

40:14.663 --> 40:16.955
I DIDN'T MEAN TO HURT YOU.

40:16.955 --> 40:18.747
I'M SURE YOU DIDN'T.

40:18.747 --> 40:20.959
I'M SURE YOU DIDN'T EVEN
THINK ABOUT ME.

40:20.959 --> 40:23.171
YOU SAW AN OPENING,
AND YOU TOOK IT.

40:25.253 --> 40:29.257
I HAVE ALWAYS WANTED TO PROTECT
YOU EVER SINCE DAD DIED.

40:29.257 --> 40:30.679
I DIDN'T WANT TO.

40:30.679 --> 40:33.011
I'M SURE
YOU DIDN'T WANT ME TO.

40:33.011 --> 40:34.312
BUT I PROMISED.

40:35.554 --> 40:38.356
[ BELL JINGLES ]

40:39.858 --> 40:41.480
[ CHILD CRIES ]
Shh!

40:41.480 --> 40:44.232
[ GUNSHOT ]

40:45.984 --> 40:47.986
THEN YOU CAME UP HERE,
AND I REALIZED...

40:47.986 --> 40:49.658
I DIDN'T HAVE TO WORRY
ANYMORE.

40:49.658 --> 40:51.199
YOU WERE OKAY.
YOU WERE FINE.

40:51.199 --> 40:52.531
YOU WERE MORE THAN FINE.

40:52.531 --> 40:54.242
YOU COULD...

40:54.242 --> 40:55.784
TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF NOW,
AND...

40:58.076 --> 40:59.417
...I DIDN'T NEED TO
ANYMORE.

41:01.920 --> 41:04.042
I NEEDED YOU TODAY.

41:04.042 --> 41:08.677
...A CHANCE
TO RIGHT OUR WRONGS,

41:08.677 --> 41:11.590
TO TRY AND CORRECT
OUR MISTAKES...

41:11.590 --> 41:13.011
[ SIGHS ]

41:13.011 --> 41:14.933
I DON'T KNOW WHO I AM
ANYMORE.

41:14.933 --> 41:19.187
NOT ANYBODY
I EVER THOUGHT I'D --

41:19.187 --> 41:22.480
I'D BE.

41:22.480 --> 41:26.064
I TRY AND MAKE THE RIGHT CHOICES
FOR MEREDITH...

41:26.064 --> 41:28.737
THE KIDS, YOU.

41:28.737 --> 41:31.660
AND, UM...

41:31.660 --> 41:33.952
I'M ANGRY ALL THE TIME.

41:33.952 --> 41:38.747
I'M MISERABLE, AND I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO WITH IT.

41:38.747 --> 41:43.171
ALL I DO IS HURT PEOPLE.

41:43.171 --> 41:46.174
THE LAST PEOPLE
I WANT TO HURT, AND I JUST...

41:49.507 --> 41:52.340
I JUST CAN'T
GET CONTROL OF IT.

41:59.437 --> 42:01.940
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO ANYMORE.

42:03.902 --> 42:06.985
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

42:06.985 --> 42:09.197
WE CALL IT ROCK BOTTOM.

42:16.825 --> 42:19.457
...A CHANCE TO TRY
AND START OVER FROM SCRATCH.
